<section
  id='case-lumastays-design'
  class='fullscreen-section'
  data-title='Case Study: Luma Stays — Web & Interaction Design | Katja Turnsek'
  data-description='Web and interaction design case study focused on accommodation browsing, booking decisions, role-based flows, responsive layouts, and a clear manager experience.'
  data-case='lumastays'
>
  <div class='rows'>
    <div class='row'>
      <h1>Web & Interaction Design</h1>
      <h2>Luma Stays - Booking Interface & User Flows</h2>

      <div class='tech-demo-wrapper'>
        <div class='tech-stack'><strong>Tools:</strong> Figma | React | Bootstrap | UX Flow</div>

        <!-- Reusable component: Demo Links -->
        <div class='demo-links' data-auto='demo' data-case='lumastays-design'></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <!-- Reusable component: Project Switcher -->
      <nav
        class='project-switcher'
        aria-label='Luma Stays sections'
        data-auto='switcher'
        data-case='lumastays'
      ></nav>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <h3>Objective</h3>
      <p>
        To shape a clear
        <strong>accommodation booking experience</strong>
        where users can browse stays, compare options, understand venue details, and move toward a
        booking with confidence. The interface also needed to support venue managers, so the design
        had to separate customer actions from listing management without making the product feel
        fragmented.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <div class='case-study-columns'>
        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <div class='case-study-text'>
            <h3>Design Focus</h3>
            <ul class='bullet-list'>
              <li>
                Designed a structured
                <strong>booking interface</strong>
                with clear hierarchy, readable content, and visible calls-to-action
              </li>
              <li>
                Created browsing patterns for
                <strong>search, filtering, venue cards, and venue detail pages</strong>
                so users can compare accommodation options quickly
              </li>
              <li>
                Shaped the booking flow around
                <strong>decision-making moments</strong>
                such as location, price, facilities, guest count, and availability
              </li>
              <li>
                Planned separate flows for
                <strong>customers and venue managers</strong>
                while keeping the visual language consistent across the app
              </li>
              <li>
                Balanced a polished travel-style interface with
                <strong>usable forms, responsive layouts, and accessible content structure</strong>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <figure class='case-study-item item-right'>
            <img
              class='thumb'
              src='{{base}}assets/images/design-lumastays-explore-600.webp'
              data-src='design-lumastays-explore-600.webp'
              data-path='assets/images'
              alt='Luma Stays explore page showing search, filters, and accommodation cards'
            />
            <figcaption class='work-caption'>Explore stays - Search and filtering UI</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <figure class='case-study-item item-left'>
            <img
              class='thumb'
              src='{{base}}assets/images/design-lumastays-booking-flow-600.webp'
              data-src='design-lumastays-booking-flow-600.webp'
              data-path='assets/images'
              alt='Luma Stays venue detail page showing booking flow and guest selection'
            />
            <figcaption class='work-caption'>Booking flow - Venue details and guest selection</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <div class='case-study-text'>
            <h3>Interaction Decisions</h3>
            <ul class='bullet-list-right'>
              <li>
                <strong>Search and filters</strong>
                are placed close to the venue grid so users can refine results without losing
                context
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Venue cards</strong>
                surface key information early, including image, title, location, price, and rating
              </li>
              <li>
                The
                <strong>venue detail page</strong>
                separates description, facilities, price, and booking actions into clear content
                areas
              </li>
              <li>
                Booking controls were kept
                <strong>direct and visible</strong>
                so users do not need to search for the next action
              </li>
              <li>
                Manager views support
                <strong>ownership, editing, and listing overview</strong>
                without interfering with the customer browsing experience
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <div class='case-study-text'>
            <h3>Role-Based Flow</h3>
            <p>
              Luma Stays needed to work for two different user types: customers booking
              accommodation and managers handling their own listings. I separated these flows so
              users can focus on the task they came for, while shared components, spacing, and
              navigation patterns keep the experience consistent across the product.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <figure class='case-study-item item-right'>
            <img
              class='thumb'
              src='{{base}}assets/images/design-lumastays-manager-dashboard-600.webp'
              data-src='design-lumastays-manager-dashboard-600.webp'
              data-path='assets/images'
              alt='Luma Stays manager dashboard showing managed venues and booking information'
            />
            <figcaption class='work-caption'>Manager dashboard - Profile and managed venues</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <h3>Reflection</h3>
      <p>
        The main design challenge was making Luma Stays feel complete without overwhelming the user.
        I focused on
        <strong>clear user flows, reusable interface patterns, responsive layouts, and role-based
          navigation</strong>. This case shows how I connect visual design with front-end structure:
        the interface is not only styled, but shaped around how users search, compare, book, and
        manage accommodation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class='back-to-work-container'>
      <a
        href='{{base}}#work'
        class='label-link back-to-work-label'
        data-back
        data-back-fallback='{{base}}#work'
        aria-label='Go back'
      >
        <svg class='icon icon-18 arrow-icon' aria-hidden='true'><use href='#i-arrow-left' /></svg>
        <span class='label-text'>Back to Work</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>